(AK)^2 (BD) + (AC)^2 (BK) + (AB)^2 (CD) &= (BC)^2 (AK)^2 + (BD)^2 (AC)^2 \\
(AK)^2 (14) + (15)^2 (6) + (13)^2 (9) &= (14)^2 (AK)^2 + (7)^2 (15)^2 \\
(AB)^2 (CD) &= (AC)^2 (BD) \\
AK &= \frac{AK}{13} \cdot \frac{AK}{15} \cdot 7 \\
K &= \frac{13 \cdot 15 \cdot 7}{AK} \\
K &= \frac{13 \cdot 15 \cdot 7}{14} \\
K &= \boxed{45}.
\end{align*}
Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{45}$.

